1
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:00,240
This is my salary card.

2
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:02,170
You can spend the money from now on.

3
00:01:03,680 --> 00:01:05,280
Currently, our cooperative

4
00:01:05,360 --> 00:01:06,490
can't pay wages yet.

5
00:01:06,880 --> 00:01:08,240
You followed me to Xia Village,

6
00:01:08,240 --> 00:01:10,120
which is already a huge sign of trust in me.

7
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:12,120
I can't let you work for free, right?

8
00:01:12,640 --> 00:01:14,700
From now on, my salary is your salary.

9
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:16,480
I know

10
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:19,400
this can't compare to your high salary in the big city.

11
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,000
But

12
00:01:20,960 --> 00:01:22,240
whatever you want to eat every day from now on,

13
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:23,160
I will make it for you.

14
00:01:23,160 --> 00:01:25,090
I will buy whatever you want to buy.

15
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:26,160
For other expenses,

16
00:01:26,160 --> 00:01:27,220
just use this card.

17
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:30,289
I asked Teacher Yin for your birthday.

18
00:01:30,360 --> 00:01:31,480
The password for this card

19
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:32,479
is your birthday.

20
00:01:40,280 --> 00:01:41,120
No, no.

21
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:42,360
I can't take this.

22
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:44,440
Just consider it my technical investment.

23
00:01:44,440 --> 00:01:45,680
If it makes money later,

24
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:46,680
just give me a cut.

25
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:48,920
I'm happy to be able to help you.

26
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:51,600
Take it.

27
00:01:53,479 --> 00:01:54,759
This is all the commitment

28
00:01:54,759 --> 00:01:56,220
I can make to you right now.

29
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:02,600
My salary card,

30
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:04,240
it's all for you to spend.

31
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:09,800
No.

32
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:11,120
Ren Zhen, wake up.

33
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:11,920
Ren Zhen.

34
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:13,480
You are here to build your career.

35
00:02:13,480 --> 00:02:15,840
The Secretary is only talking to you about business.

36
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:17,570
Don't imagine a sweet romance.

37
00:02:21,640 --> 00:02:23,440
What do you want to eat tomorrow?

38
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:36,000
Brother Secretary,

39
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:38,060
is that really what you told Ren Zhen?

40
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:40,320
What's wrong?

41
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:42,040
That sounds a bit weird.

42
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:44,960
You obviously went to explain the pay.

43
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:48,170
Why did it sound like a marriage proposal in a TV show?

44
00:02:50,640 --> 00:02:51,360
Did it?

45
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:52,640
Yes.

46
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:54,600
It was so weird.

47
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:56,040
Well,

48
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:58,120
but those are my true feelings.

49
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:00,560
I still

50
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:02,320
haven't received my salary.

51
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:05,410
Why don't you take responsibility for me too?

52
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:06,520
You?

53
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:09,360
Your dad dumped you on me back then

54
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:10,920
and told me to train you.

55
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:12,360
You can leave,

56
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:13,680
but Ren Zhen can't.

57
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:28,280
It does seem a bit weird.

58
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:33,820
You can film more around here.

59
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:37,940
Let's go to the goji berry farm later.

60
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:38,920
Sure.

61
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:41,480
We'll film the villagers' daily lives today.

62
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:42,140
No problem.

63
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:43,440
I've already talked to them.

64
00:03:43,440 --> 00:03:44,520
They are very enthusiastic

65
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:46,200
and said they'll fully cooperate.

66
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:47,160
Great.

67
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:49,620
We know about Xinjiang and goji berries,

68
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:51,280
but we've always had stereotypes

69
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:52,840
about its culture and customs.

70
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:53,570
For example,

71
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:55,400
that they ride camels to school,

72
00:03:55,640 --> 00:03:57,760
or do the neck dance and stuff.

73
00:03:58,600 --> 00:03:59,079
Then,

74
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,400
do you think so too?

75
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:02,400
Of course I don't.

76
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:04,080
As for information on the internet,

77
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:06,480
you still need to be able to distinguish it.

78
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:09,440
It's just that there are too few people like me.

79
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:11,760
We must make our voices heard

80
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:14,560
and strive to be the first to enter Xia Village.

81
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,000
Grandpa Bate,

82
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:23,880
Grandpa Bate, you don't need to be nervous.

83
00:04:23,880 --> 00:04:25,240
Just pretend we don't exist

84
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:26,840
and do what you normally do.

85
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:29,720
Are we good?

86
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:42,080
Wrap it up.

87
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,520
Eat the grapes but don't spit out the skins.

88
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:49,240
Don't eat the grapes but spit out the skins.

89
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:51,120
Eat the grapes but don't spit out the skins.

90
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:51,800
Don't spit it.

91
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:53,080
Don't eat the grapes but spit out the skins.

92
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:55,480
Eat the grapes but don't spit out the skins.

93
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:07,130
Auntie Guli,

94
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:08,530
act more naturally.

95
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,240
Be natural.

96
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:10,160
Yes, smile.

97
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:15,840
No,

98
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:17,640
just pick them like you normally do.

99
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:18,770
Don't strike a pose.

100
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:20,880
Strike a pose?

101
00:05:30,240 --> 00:05:30,840
This...

102
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:35,680
We are done shooting.

103
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:36,120
Are we done shooting?

104
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:38,050
We are not shooting anymore today.

105
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,520
How can we use these?

106
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:46,159
Here.

107
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:47,080
Time to eat.

108
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:49,200
Try some.

109
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:50,380
Have some meat.

110
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:52,640
I have no appetite.

111
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:54,320
The stuff we shot today,

112
00:05:54,640 --> 00:05:56,159
won't it just make the outside stereotypes

113
00:05:56,159 --> 00:05:57,520
even worse?

114
00:05:57,960 --> 00:05:59,620
You still need to eat a little.

115
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:00,320
Come here.

116
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:12,410
You're really good at cooking.

117
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:14,280
If you like it,

118
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:16,140
I'll cook it for you every day.

119
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:27,480
Come on.

120
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:28,920
Do you all have

121
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:30,720
camera shyness?

122
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:33,080
There are so many staged videos online.

123
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:34,000
What we want is

124
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:35,960
a lively and natural feel.

125
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:37,680
You guys all

126
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:39,000
freeze up on camera.

127
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:40,440
How is this going to work?

128
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:43,400
Right.

129
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:45,240
I can just hide the camera.

130
00:06:57,640 --> 00:06:58,440
Let's stop filming.

131
00:06:58,440 --> 00:07:00,700
I need to hurry up and pick the ripe fruit.

132
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:02,120
The weather is great.

133
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:04,280
The goji berries are big and red.

134
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:06,040
Have another taste.

135
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:08,400
They're even better than a few days ago.

136
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:16,240
Goji berries grown in alkaline soil are the sweetest.

137
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:18,280
These drink water from the Tianshan Mountains.

138
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:20,480
A darling raised in the northwest wind.

139
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:24,000
What is this?

140
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:26,640
Nothing.

141
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:28,450
I'll leave you to it.

142
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:30,000
We're leaving now. Bye, Aunt Guli.

143
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:30,600
Bye.

144
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:35,880
Come back.

145
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:36,880
Ayijiang.

146
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,330
How can that thing move?

147
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:39,620
Come back here.

148
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:42,720
I left it facing Dad's desk

149
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:43,720
for an hour.

150
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:45,330
Do you think this will work?

151
00:07:45,960 --> 00:07:51,080
When the green apple turns red.

152
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:52,360
That works perfectly.

153
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:52,920
By the way,

154
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:54,040
you can film me.

155
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:55,200
I can ride horses,

156
00:07:55,320 --> 00:07:57,000
wrestle, and feed lambs.

157
00:07:57,520 --> 00:07:59,250
Okay, we'll film you next time.

158
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:04,400
When the green apples turn red.

159
00:08:08,440 --> 00:08:09,970
Grandpa Bate, how old is it?

160
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,130
Less than a year old.

161
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:17,490
What is that girl doing?

162
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:20,120
She... she's looking for eagles.

163
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:21,160
That machine in her hand

164
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:23,090
can detect the presence of eagles.

165
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:25,120
That's too much trouble.

166
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:26,880
I have an old friend

167
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,080
named Aerdin.

168
00:08:28,840 --> 00:08:29,440
He can tell

169
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:32,880
where eagles are just by smelling.

170
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:33,880
That's amazing.

171
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:34,799
Of course.

172
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:36,720
Grandpa Bate,

173
00:08:37,159 --> 00:08:37,760
look,

174
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:39,740
this is a photo of you and the lamb.

175
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:46,520
You're here

176
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:49,200
tricking the old man into taking pictures.

177
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:51,640
I have to say,

178
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,320
it looks really good.

179
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:55,240
How is it?

180
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:56,160
Do you like it?

181
00:08:56,160 --> 00:08:57,560
I like it. It looks good.

182
00:08:58,440 --> 00:08:59,520
Very handsome.
